The paper proposes a new Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) framework for face recognition using hyperspectral imaging systems. This involves selecting the optimal spectral bands to obtain the best performance, which is achieved through a structural sparsity learning technique. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves regularization techniques and automatic selection of spectral bands, which are common in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
